Types of Mystery Boxes
1. 🎉 Starter Box (cheap / entry level)
Low price
Mostly common themes
Small chance at rare

👉 Gets users hooked

2. 💎 Premium Box
Mid-tier price
Better odds for rare themes
Some exclusive items
3. 🔥 Legendary Box
High price
Guaranteed high-quality rewards
Chance at ultra-rare themes
4. ⏳ Limited-Time Boxes
Event-based (holiday, viral trends)
Exclusive drops
Creates urgency (FOMO)
5. 🎮 Activity Boxes (FREE)
Earn by:
Going live
Watching streams
Daily login

👉 Keeps users engaged without paying

🎨 Reward Types (what users actually get)
Profile/Broadcast themes (main reward)
Animated effects (glow, particles, aura)
Badges / status icons
Username styles
Limited edition visuals

👉 Make rewards visible to others = drives purchases

📊 Rarity System (VERY important)

Use tiers like:

Common (60–70%)
Rare (20–25%)
Epic (8–10%)
Legendary (1–3%)
Mythic (0.1–1%)

👉 Show odds clearly to avoid legal/payment issues

💰 Monetization Strategy
Price boxes using your coin system
Bundle deals:
“Buy 5 get 1 free”
First-time bonus:
Guaranteed rare item
⚠️ CRITICAL (don’t skip this)

Mystery boxes can be seen as gambling mechanics.

To stay safe:

Show drop rates publicly
Avoid “real money gambling” language
Make sure users always get something
Consider age restrictions if needed